To address the issue described in the bug report, we need to modify the code to conditionally set the `title` attribute based on whether the `children` of `Menu.Item` is a pure string or not. This will help avoid the problem of duplicate text and unwanted title tooltips.

### Bug Scenario Description and Root Cause

1. **Bug Scenario Description:**
   - The images show a dropdown menu where hovering over an item displays a tooltip with the same text as the menu item itself. This is problematic when the text is long and gets truncated, as the tooltip is meant to show the full text.
   - The tooltip appears even when the text is not truncated, which violates the WCAG principle of avoiding repetitive text.

2. **Root Cause:**
   - The `title` attribute is being set unconditionally, which causes the tooltip to appear even when the text is not truncated or when the text is the same as the menu item.

### Bug Fix

We will modify the `render` method in `src/menu/view/item.jsx` to set the `title` attribute only when the `children` is a pure string and potentially truncated.

